## TESTING STRATEGY (ENTERPRISE TDD)

### TDD Workflow Implementation
*[CUSTOMIZE: Define your specific TDD implementation]*
```
1. Write Failing Test:
   - [test_command] [specific_test_file]
   - Verify test fails for the right reason
   
2. Write Minimal Implementation:
   - Code just enough to make test pass
   - No premature optimization
   
3. Refactor Safely:
   - Improve code while keeping tests green
   - Run full test suite after refactoring
   
4. Integration Testing:
   - Test component interactions
   - Use real dependencies, no mocks
   
5. End-to-End Testing:
   - Test complete user workflows
   - Verify business value delivery
```

### Test Data Management
*[CUSTOMIZE: Define test data strategies]*
```
- Test Database: [separate test database strategy]
- Test Data: [factories, fixtures, or generated data]
- Cleanup Strategy: [how tests clean up after themselves]
- Isolation: [how tests avoid interfering with each other]

Example:
- Test DB: Separate PostgreSQL instance with Docker
- Test Data: Factory Boy with realistic fake data
- Cleanup: Automatic transaction rollback after each test
- Isolation: Each test runs in its own transaction
```

### Performance & Load Testing
*[CUSTOMIZE: Define performance testing approach]*
```
- Performance Targets: [response times, throughput, etc.]
- Load Testing Tools: [k6, JMeter, Artillery, etc.]
- Monitoring: [APM tools, custom metrics]
- Regression Testing: [automated performance regression detection]

Example:
- Targets: 95th percentile < 200ms, 1000 concurrent users
- Tools: k6 for load testing, Prometheus for monitoring
- CI Integration: Performance tests in staging environment
- Alerts: Automatic alerts for 20% performance degradation
```

